<p>In some countries, bananas used for cooking may be called ‚Äúplantains‚Äù, distinguishing them from dessert bananas. The fruit is variable in size, color, and firmness, but is usually elongated and curved, with soft flesh rich in starch covered in rind, which may be green, yellow, red, purple, or brown when ripe.</p>
